-- Angelini to Invest $300 Mln in Chile Copper Mine, Republica Says
-- B y   M i c h a e l   S m i t h
-- 2011-12-18T15:18:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-18/angelini-to-invest-300-mln-in-chile-copper-mine-republica-says.html
Chile ’s Angelini Group plans to
invest more than $300 million to develop a copper mine in
northern Chile, La Republica reported.  Roberto Angelini, chairman of the group’s  Empresas Copec
SA , said in an interview that the investment will be to develop
the Diego de Almagro copper deposit in the Atacama region of
Chile, the Colombian newspaper reported on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
